Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State will lead a high-level 49-member campaign council, appointed by the Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress, for the Edo State Governorship Election, the party has said. A statement issued by the Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the party, Yekini Sabena, on Thursday, listed other members to include Governor Hope Uzodinma of Imo State, who was named Deputy Chairman and Abbas Braimoh, Secretary. According to the statement, the council was formed following “the approval for the constitution of a National Campaign Council for the 19th September, 2020 Governorship Election, by the National Chairman of the APC Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee, H.E. Mai Mala Buni.” “The campaign council will be inaugurated on Monday, 6th July 2020 at the Party’s National Secretariat,” it said. Full list:
